WEBVTT

00:14.931 --> 00:16.850
- Heidi. Heidi.

00:16.891 --> 00:18.435
[birds chirping]

00:18.476 --> 00:20.687
[tranquil harp music]

00:20.729 --> 00:22.605
- Bumper Allen.

00:22.647 --> 00:24.024
* *

00:24.065 --> 00:27.027
[heartbeat pumping]

00:27.068 --> 00:29.612
[tense music]

00:29.654 --> 00:32.032
You are being deported
by the German government.

00:32.073 --> 00:33.867
* *

00:33.908 --> 00:35.201
[heartbeat quickens]

00:35.243 --> 00:36.828
[high-pitched tone]

00:36.870 --> 00:38.079
- Ahh!

00:38.997 --> 00:40.123
You guys are all here.

00:40.165 --> 00:41.875
I had a nightmare
about being deported.

00:41.916 --> 00:43.168
- It wasn't a nightmare.

00:43.209 --> 00:44.627
You were having a recap.

00:47.422 --> 00:49.883
This is your official
Abschiebungsbefehl.

00:49.924 --> 00:51.801
- Obviously, it is totally,

00:51.843 --> 00:53.720
but you should probably
explain it for Heidi.

00:53.762 --> 00:56.181
- It's your official
deportation notice.

00:56.222 --> 00:59.142
It says you have to leave
the country in six hours.

00:59.184 --> 01:01.102
Also, happy German Unity Day.

01:01.144 --> 01:02.520
- How did this even happen?

01:02.562 --> 01:04.230
- You didn't apply
for your work visa.

01:04.272 --> 01:06.691
- Not to ladle
another turd dumpling

01:06.733 --> 01:07.942
into the crap soup,

01:07.984 --> 01:10.028
but this means
you can't perform at Unity Day

01:10.070 --> 01:12.405
since it's after
the deportation deadline.

01:12.447 --> 01:14.199
If you try,
you will get arrested.

01:14.240 --> 01:16.076
- I was getting used
to a routine.

01:16.117 --> 01:17.535
Heidi buys pastries,

01:17.577 --> 01:19.412
Pieter whines
that you are his only hope,

01:19.454 --> 01:20.914
we prod you
to be a better person,

01:20.955 --> 01:23.124
and we have fun in the process.

01:24.084 --> 01:25.168
- No.

01:25.210 --> 01:26.586
The old Bumper would be crying

01:26.628 --> 01:28.129
in a clean dumpster right now,

01:28.171 --> 01:30.090
but I am not turning myself in.

01:30.131 --> 01:32.467
I am getting my moment
in the spotlight.

01:32.509 --> 01:34.719
I wanna take it all in
and wonder,

01:34.761 --> 01:36.763
can a spotlight
give you a sunburn?

01:36.805 --> 01:39.265
How does light work?

01:39.307 --> 01:40.433
It doesn't matter.

01:40.475 --> 01:41.935
We gotta get creative
right now,

01:41.976 --> 01:43.353
figure out a "solush."

01:43.395 --> 01:44.729
Because I'm not leaving
without a fight.

01:44.771 --> 01:47.440
- Maybe--
maybe we could just explain

01:47.482 --> 01:49.275
our situation and ask
for a visa extension

01:49.317 --> 01:50.985
at the Rathaus.

01:51.027 --> 01:52.904
- Yes, Heidi, the Rathaus.

01:52.946 --> 01:54.447
The Rathaus?
Okay.

01:54.489 --> 01:56.408
Well, this will be easy.
Chuck E. Cheese is a friend.

01:56.449 --> 01:57.742
- Oh, you're right.

01:57.784 --> 01:59.744
We should all give it
one more try.

01:59.786 --> 02:01.371
- Well, we don't have
that much time.

02:01.413 --> 02:03.915
You have a costume fitting
in an hour,

02:03.957 --> 02:05.625
so let's see what we can do.

02:05.667 --> 02:08.211
And in the meantime, let's keep
all of this information quiet.

02:08.253 --> 02:10.463
- Okay. Let's go.

02:10.505 --> 02:12.465
Also, maybe we
shouldn't tell anyone

02:12.507 --> 02:15.301
that I sleep in my pants
and my shoes like a fireman.

02:15.343 --> 02:18.138
[upbeat spacey music]

02:18.179 --> 02:24.644
* *

02:26.021 --> 02:27.147
- Why are we nervous?

02:27.188 --> 02:28.273
It's our dad.

02:28.314 --> 02:29.441
He can't still be mad at us.

02:29.482 --> 02:31.735
Just--just be cool.

02:31.776 --> 02:32.986
- Oh, scoot over.

02:33.028 --> 02:34.821
You know how much he enjoys
negative space.

02:34.863 --> 02:36.990
- Right, because it reflects
the emptiness...

02:37.032 --> 02:38.491
both: Of the human soul.

02:38.533 --> 02:40.410
- Good call.
- Thank you.

02:40.452 --> 02:43.496
[line ringing]

02:45.248 --> 02:46.458
- Klaus!
- Hi there!

02:46.499 --> 02:48.626
- My man.
- You big guy.

02:48.668 --> 02:50.462
- What is the meaning
of this call?

02:50.503 --> 02:52.047
You're disturbing me.

02:52.088 --> 02:53.673
- Okay. We'll make it quick.

02:53.715 --> 02:55.842
My client, Bumper,
whom you may remember,

02:55.884 --> 02:58.595
is, unfortunately, being
threatened with deportation.

02:58.636 --> 03:00.347
- Can you make some calls?

03:00.388 --> 03:02.682
You have friends
in the government, right?

03:02.724 --> 03:05.685
- Of course I have friends
in the government.

03:05.727 --> 03:09.105
Who do you think
tipped them off?

03:09.147 --> 03:11.691
- Wait,
you got Bumper deported?

03:11.733 --> 03:16.613
- After Bumper made me angry
walking off my set,

03:16.654 --> 03:18.990
I vowed to get back at him,

03:19.032 --> 03:22.285
and there is nothing
my children can do.

03:22.327 --> 03:23.953
Nothing.

03:25.163 --> 03:27.582
How do--how do I get off?

03:27.624 --> 03:29.167
I don't want to be here.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.418
[phone clicks]

03:31.503 --> 03:33.922
- God. He really is a dick.

03:39.302 --> 03:40.553
- Hello.

03:40.595 --> 03:42.222
This is Bumper Allen,
and he would like

03:42.263 --> 03:44.391
to apply for a visa extension.

03:44.432 --> 03:45.975
- I really want to help you.

03:46.017 --> 03:47.310
- Okay. Then do.

03:47.352 --> 03:49.062
- But if you're beyond
your 90 days,

03:49.104 --> 03:50.522
my hands are tied.

03:50.563 --> 03:54.901
In Germany, paperwork is king,
and I'm but a loyal serf.

03:54.943 --> 03:56.236
Except on the weekends,

03:56.277 --> 03:58.822
then it's just Hilda
being Hilda.

03:58.863 --> 04:02.117
- There's nothing you can do?
Are you serious?

04:02.158 --> 04:03.535
- I'm German.

04:03.576 --> 04:05.286
Of course I'm serious.

04:08.248 --> 04:10.792
- I can't believe this might be
my last day in Berlin.

04:11.751 --> 04:13.420
I freaking love this place.

04:13.461 --> 04:18.216
The parks,
the high-calorie street food.

04:18.258 --> 04:21.136
Most of all, I love that it
made me my favorite version

04:21.177 --> 04:22.595
of myself by far.

04:22.637 --> 04:25.265
- I don't want you to go.

04:25.306 --> 04:26.349
Since you got here,

04:26.391 --> 04:28.852
my world has been
a lot brighter.

04:28.893 --> 04:30.770
The hell are you gonna
do back in America, huh?

04:30.812 --> 04:33.273
Just go off and be friends
with people named

04:33.314 --> 04:35.859
Brittany or Luke or something?
[scoffs]

04:35.900 --> 04:36.943
Stupid.

04:36.985 --> 04:38.486
- I am so sorry.

04:39.571 --> 04:40.864
I messed everything up.

04:40.905 --> 04:42.198
- Don't apologize.

04:42.240 --> 04:43.992
You didn't mess anything up.

04:44.034 --> 04:46.453
You know, watching you has

04:46.494 --> 04:50.373
made me want
to get out of my own way

04:50.415 --> 04:52.584
so I can be up there someday.

04:52.625 --> 04:55.128
Being around you has taught
me to be brave enough

04:55.170 --> 04:57.339
to step into my own shoes.

04:58.715 --> 05:01.885
What do you say,
for old time's sake?

05:01.926 --> 05:03.386
- I mean, of course.

05:04.471 --> 05:05.805
- Sit next to me.

05:05.847 --> 05:07.015
Oh.

05:07.057 --> 05:09.184
This might be the last time
our butts touch.

05:09.225 --> 05:11.686
- That is so sad.
- Hmm.

05:11.728 --> 05:14.564
- So what should we sing?

05:14.606 --> 05:19.152
- "Boulevard of Broken Dreams"
or "Walking on Sunshine,'

05:19.194 --> 05:21.905
but we scream "not"
at the start of every chorus.

05:21.946 --> 05:25.158
- If you are leaving here
a broken dreamer,

05:25.200 --> 05:27.702
I have just the song.

05:27.744 --> 05:30.830
[playing "Don't Fall in Love
with a Dreamer"]

05:30.872 --> 05:34.334
* *

05:34.376 --> 05:37.837
* Just look at you *

05:37.879 --> 05:39.172
* *

05:39.214 --> 05:42.175
* Sitting there *

05:42.217 --> 05:45.637
* You never looked
better than tonight *

05:45.679 --> 05:46.763
- I actually don't
know the words.

05:46.805 --> 05:50.767
* And it'd be so easy *

05:50.809 --> 05:54.312
* To tell you I'd stay *

05:54.354 --> 05:59.859
* Like I've done
so many times *

05:59.901 --> 06:05.573
both: * Don't fall in love
with a dreamer *

06:05.615 --> 06:11.162
* 'Cause he'll always
take you in *

06:11.204 --> 06:18.211
* Just when you think
you've really changed him *

06:18.253 --> 06:23.633
* He'll leave you again *

06:23.675 --> 06:29.514
* Don't fall in love
with a dreamer *

06:29.556 --> 06:35.186
* 'Cause he'll break
you every time *

06:35.228 --> 06:36.604
* *

06:36.646 --> 06:39.649
- * Oh, put out the light *

06:39.691 --> 06:42.318
- * Just hold on *

06:42.360 --> 06:48.450
both: * Before we say goodbye *

06:48.491 --> 06:53.788
* *

06:55.623 --> 06:58.835
[applause]

07:00.045 --> 07:01.129
- Thank you.

07:01.171 --> 07:03.131
- Obviously,
all the romantic stuff

07:03.173 --> 07:04.758
was just written by Kenny.

07:04.799 --> 07:07.802
- Was there romantic stuff
in that song?

07:07.844 --> 07:12.474
I just thought it was
about doors and lights...

07:12.515 --> 07:13.850
and stuff.

07:16.519 --> 07:19.022
- Hey, get away from my piano.

07:19.064 --> 07:20.190
- Okay.

07:20.231 --> 07:21.608
- If you don't want us
to play the piano,

07:21.649 --> 07:23.401
just don't leave the piano.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.111
- Is that even his piano?

07:25.153 --> 07:28.114
- [whispering] I hope Pieter
and Thea had more success.

07:30.658 --> 07:32.410
- Great. You're here.

07:32.452 --> 07:34.412
Well, try some costume options.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.831
The Unity Day committee over
there will approve the look,

07:36.873 --> 07:38.708
and we will be off
to the races.

07:38.750 --> 07:40.251
Assume the position, please.

07:40.293 --> 07:42.253
- Okay.

07:42.295 --> 07:43.922
[loud bang]

07:46.091 --> 07:48.134
- Well, you don't need
to stand like that.

07:48.176 --> 07:49.386
- Oh.

07:49.427 --> 07:51.179
It must mean something
different in America.

07:52.472 --> 07:53.348
- I'm sorry we're late.
Okay.

07:53.390 --> 07:54.474
We got a big failure.

07:54.516 --> 07:56.309
We totally botched the--
- Pieter.

07:56.351 --> 07:58.478
This is the Unity Day costumer.

07:58.520 --> 08:02.315
And over there are the members
of the Unity Day committee.

08:02.357 --> 08:04.067
- Of course.

08:04.109 --> 08:07.570
Oh, we are excited
to get Bumper dressed up

08:07.612 --> 08:08.988
for a big event

08:09.030 --> 08:11.825
with absolutely no other
complications whatsoever.

08:11.866 --> 08:13.660
- Yeah.
- Uh-huh.

08:13.702 --> 08:15.537
- [through teeth]
Any luck at the Rathaus?

08:15.578 --> 08:17.205
- No.
And what are you doing?

08:17.247 --> 08:18.665
- I'm smiling.

08:18.707 --> 08:20.875
- So any luck with Klaus?

08:20.917 --> 08:22.377
- No. In fact, he's the one

08:22.419 --> 08:24.587
that got the government
to boil your spaetzle.

08:24.629 --> 08:27.173
- D'oh! Klaus!

08:27.215 --> 08:28.466
Also, what is a spaetzle?

08:28.508 --> 08:29.843
- Oh, it's a homemade noodle.

08:29.884 --> 08:31.886
- I'm gonna call Klaus back
and tell him off.

08:31.928 --> 08:33.930
And, oh, my face hurts.

08:33.972 --> 08:37.017
It must be exhausting
to be a nice person or a wolf.

08:38.018 --> 08:40.979
- Well, well, well, if it isn't
so many blueberry muffins

08:41.021 --> 08:42.689
stealing half of my spotlight.

08:42.731 --> 08:43.982
What next?

08:44.024 --> 08:45.233
You're going to steal
my Unity Day look?

08:45.275 --> 08:48.361
- I hope not because
I can't pull off white.

08:48.403 --> 08:50.030
It washes me out.

08:50.071 --> 08:51.740
- Gisela, excuse us a minute.

08:51.781 --> 08:53.575
- Oh, no problem.

08:53.616 --> 08:56.745
I'll just cease to exist
for 60 seconds.

08:56.786 --> 08:58.163
both: Okay.

09:00.790 --> 09:02.667
- We need to talk.

09:02.709 --> 09:03.752
- You have been doing squats.

09:03.793 --> 09:05.462
- Several thousand a day. Yes.

09:05.503 --> 09:06.588
- I think I know
how to save you

09:06.629 --> 09:08.381
from being deported.

09:08.423 --> 09:09.549
- What?

09:09.591 --> 09:11.551
- You have to marry Thea.

09:11.593 --> 09:13.595
[tense music]

09:20.268 --> 09:22.103
- Marry Thea?

09:22.145 --> 09:25.315
- Seeing Gisela's white dress,
it just clicked.

09:25.357 --> 09:28.109
If you marry a citizen,
you can stay in the country.

09:28.151 --> 09:29.152
- Okay.

09:29.194 --> 09:31.780
I don't know
if you know this or not,

09:31.821 --> 09:33.823
but Thea and I are not in love.

09:34.866 --> 09:36.659
Is this what you want me to do?

09:36.701 --> 09:39.245
- It is if it keeps you
in Germany.

09:39.287 --> 09:42.165
- How long would we have
to pretend to be a couple?

09:42.207 --> 09:45.710
What happens if I fall in love
with somebody else

09:45.752 --> 09:47.128
or I already am?
Never mind.

09:47.170 --> 09:48.963
I mean, would Thea
even go for this?

09:49.005 --> 09:51.132
She once called me
"Mr. Potato Head

09:51.174 --> 09:52.842
if he couldn't grow
that mustache."

09:55.887 --> 09:59.015
- Thea,
do you wanna marry Bumper

09:59.057 --> 10:00.350
so he can stay in the country?

10:00.392 --> 10:01.768
- Sure.

10:01.810 --> 10:03.228
- You'd do this for me
even though we're not in love?

10:03.269 --> 10:05.397
- I'm an anarchist,
and I hate my dad.

10:05.438 --> 10:07.315
Those feelings
are as legitimate as love.

10:07.357 --> 10:09.651
- Well,
let's get you guys married

10:09.693 --> 10:11.319
and get you to the stage!

10:11.361 --> 10:13.238
- Okay. Yeah.

10:13.279 --> 10:14.656
I guess there's
no other option.

10:14.698 --> 10:16.825
- What every girl wants
to hear in her wedding day.

10:16.866 --> 10:17.909
- Oh, great.

10:17.951 --> 10:19.869
This is gonna be great.

10:22.706 --> 10:24.082
Let's go.

10:24.124 --> 10:26.543
- Go. Okay, let's go!
Yes, run, run, run!

10:26.584 --> 10:28.670
[energetic synth music]

10:28.712 --> 10:29.838
* *

10:29.879 --> 10:31.047
- We'll go back to the Rathaus

10:31.089 --> 10:32.674
and get you married
before the concert.

10:32.716 --> 10:34.009
- But we have to make it
look real

10:34.050 --> 10:35.468
so they don't think
we're committing fraud.

10:35.510 --> 10:36.803
Bumper's in day-old pants,

10:36.845 --> 10:38.346
and Thea looks like
she's two wheels short

10:38.388 --> 10:40.473
of motorcycle cosplay.

10:40.515 --> 10:41.891
- I know who can help.

10:41.933 --> 10:44.644
* *

10:44.686 --> 10:45.770
Ursula.

10:45.812 --> 10:47.480
* *

10:47.522 --> 10:48.648
Where's your lost and found?

10:48.690 --> 10:50.734
- My armoire is your armoire.

10:50.775 --> 10:52.402
Please.

10:52.444 --> 10:56.448
* *

10:58.199 --> 10:59.701
- Oh, Thea.

10:59.743 --> 11:01.745
You look so beautiful.

11:01.786 --> 11:03.621
How do you feel
about your big day?

11:03.663 --> 11:06.291
Are you nervous at all?

11:06.332 --> 11:07.375
- A little.

11:07.417 --> 11:10.295
- Oh, well...

11:10.337 --> 11:11.921
you can borrow
my Dove deodorant.

11:11.963 --> 11:13.381
It keeps me from getting
the nervous sweats

11:13.423 --> 11:15.383
when I pretend to be
a guest at a fancy hotel

11:15.425 --> 11:16.843
to use their bathroom.

11:17.927 --> 11:21.056
- I feel excited
to destroy my father

11:21.097 --> 11:23.266
and make a mockery
of the German state.

11:28.480 --> 11:30.231
Are you okay?

11:30.273 --> 11:32.233
- I know I suggested all this,

11:32.275 --> 11:35.320
but it didn't feel real
until right now.

11:35.362 --> 11:37.781
And well, I--

11:37.822 --> 11:41.701
I think Bumper
will make a good husband.

11:41.743 --> 11:45.246
Yeah. He seems like the type
to announce blueberry pancakes,

11:45.288 --> 11:46.956
but then have none
of the ingredients,

11:46.998 --> 11:48.416
so you end up
eating stale toast,

11:48.458 --> 11:50.502
but the sentiment was there,
you know?

11:51.836 --> 11:54.130
- Yeah. He's not my type.

11:54.172 --> 11:57.759
If the temperature
of a cave was a person,

11:57.801 --> 11:59.928
that's my type.

11:59.969 --> 12:02.597
- Yeah. That makes sense.

12:02.639 --> 12:04.891
I'm kind of the opposite.

12:04.933 --> 12:07.727
- Thank you
for being my maid of honor

12:07.769 --> 12:09.020
and my friend.

12:09.062 --> 12:11.690
My other friends
are exactly like me,

12:11.731 --> 12:14.067
and it can get tedious.

12:14.943 --> 12:17.112
I like seeing the world
through your eyes.

12:17.153 --> 12:19.531
- Well, thank you
for showing me

12:19.572 --> 12:22.701
that somebody like you
could like somebody like me.

12:22.742 --> 12:23.910
- Come on.

12:23.952 --> 12:25.203
- Seriously, you have taught me

12:25.245 --> 12:28.164
to be more confident
and more myself.

12:28.206 --> 12:31.126
Ugh. I cannot wait to tell
my middle school bullies

12:31.167 --> 12:33.628
that I have a cool friend.
- [laughs]

12:33.670 --> 12:35.839
Luckily, they're all selling
essential oils on Facebook,

12:35.880 --> 12:37.841
so they're super easy to find.

12:40.844 --> 12:43.388
[sentimental music]

12:43.430 --> 12:44.639
* *

12:44.681 --> 12:46.016
- Okay.

12:47.726 --> 12:49.644
- Now for the final touch.

12:49.686 --> 12:51.896
* *

12:51.938 --> 12:54.691
Horns under the lace
or poking through?

12:54.733 --> 12:55.900
- I can't believe an hour ago,

12:55.942 --> 12:57.444
I was mentally packing
my socks,

12:57.485 --> 12:59.946
and now I'm getting married
to Thea.

12:59.988 --> 13:01.865
This is so crazy.

13:01.906 --> 13:04.200
But you know, I've come so far.

13:04.242 --> 13:06.411
The new Bumper
doesn't back down from a fight.

13:06.453 --> 13:08.455
- Man, my client
and my best friend

13:08.496 --> 13:10.915
is going to be my brother?
Wow.

13:10.957 --> 13:12.500
The rest of the world
might still hate me,

13:12.542 --> 13:15.628
but I don't care because I have
you and you have my sister.

13:15.670 --> 13:17.672
- Did you just call me
your best friend and brother?

13:17.714 --> 13:18.965
- I did.

13:19.007 --> 13:21.843
[laughs]
- [grunts]

13:21.885 --> 13:23.636
I got you. [laughs]

13:23.678 --> 13:25.513
Yes. Yes.

13:25.555 --> 13:26.514
Oh, my God.

13:26.556 --> 13:27.849
Christmases
are gonna be so fun.

13:27.891 --> 13:29.768
- Oh. Yes, they are.

13:29.809 --> 13:31.019
- You know who
we should invite?

13:31.061 --> 13:32.520
- Who?
- To Christmas?

13:32.562 --> 13:33.897
Heidi.

13:33.938 --> 13:35.732
So she's not, like,
out in the cold

13:35.774 --> 13:37.025
with her cute little nose

13:37.067 --> 13:38.735
pressed against
the frosted glass,

13:38.777 --> 13:39.903
like, "Please, sir,

